AED 20,000-22,000 per month equivilent to circa £39,000-£43,000 p/a
Our client is an employer of choice in this growing events hot bed in the Middle East.  They are a global brand and have an extensive portfolio of publications, conferences and exhibitions.
These Marketing Manager roles are based one in Dubai and one in Abu Dhabi and each will work on one of our client’s prestigious B2B exhibitions.  Both events are market leaders in their respective industries and bring together a raft of superior, international exhibitors and visitors. You will be responsible for developing marketing plans and creative briefs to promote the brand, undertake competitor analysis and develop a through understanding of the event and is exhibitor and visitor audiences.  You will contribute to budget decisions and ensure that all activities are carried out on time, within budget and that key objectives are achieved.
To be considered, you must have a minimum of 2-3 years marketing management experience gained in a B2B exhibitions environment.  We are looking for somebody with a good mix of traditional and digital marketing skills including social media and the ability to create innovative ideas to maintain the event’s elevated status.  If you are a team player with excellent interpersonal skills and good attention to detail then please get in touch.
This client does offer relocation assistance to candidates currently living outside of the UAE
